{{short description|Sindarin, Quenya, and Adûnaic word}}
'''''an''''' is a preposition meaning "to, towards, for" in [[Sindarin]].<ref name=lang>''[[The Languages of Tolkien's Middle-earth]]'' by [[Ruth S. Noel]]</ref> In [[Quenya]] the preposition means "for" or "because".<ref>{{RGEO|Namarie}}, line 9</ref>

When used as a prefix, '''''an-''''' means "by" or "with" in [[Sindarin]].<ref>[http://www.jrrvf.com/hisweloke/sindar/online/sindar/dict-sd-en.html Hiswelókë's Sindarin Dictionary] compiled by [[Didier Willis]]</ref>

In [[Adûnaic]] ''an-'' or '''n-'' means "of"<ref name=lang/>

